# Ansible Playbook is an ordered lists of tasks, saved so we can run those tasks in that order repeatedly.

# Playbooks in Ansible are written in YAML format and easy to read. YAML means "Yet Another Markup Language".

# A YAML file starts with a "---" at the top.

# A playbook is consists of n muber of plays.

# In a play, you can have n number of tasks.

# Playbook example:

---
- name: First Ansible Playbook
  hosts: all

  vars:
    file_name: hello_var.txt

  tasks:
    - name: Copy a file
      ansible.builtin.copy:
        src: "{{ file_name }}"
        dest: /home/iwbandara/
        owner: iwbandara
        group: iwbandara
        mode: '0777'
